{"title": "Trivia (1917) And More Trivia (1921)", "description": "Logan Pearsall Smith (1865-1946) was an American-born British essayist who was known for his epigrams and aphorisms, often humorous. This recording is of two of his collections of these bon mots. For example: \u201cThese pieces of moral prose have been written, dear Reader, by a large Carnivorous Mammal, belonging to that suborder of the Animal Kingdom which includes also the Orang-outang, the tusked Gorilla, the Baboon with his bright blue and scarlet bottom, and the long-eared Chimpanzee.\u201d ( Author's Note and david wales)", "duration": 12695, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12109", "name": "Logan Pearsall Smith"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt13/triviamoretrivia_1606.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "David Wales"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Wales"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "DaveC"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Bibliographical Note; Preface; Author's Note", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/triviaandmoretrivia_1606_librivox/triviamoretrivia_00_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 104}, {"section": 1, "title": "Trivia: Book 1", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/triviaandmoretrivia_1606_librivox/triviamoretrivia_01_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3098}, {"section": 2, "title": "Trivia: Book 2", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/triviaandmoretrivia_1606_librivox/triviamoretrivia_02_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2948}, {"section": 3, "title": "More Trivia: Part 1", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/triviaandmoretrivia_1606_librivox/triviamoretrivia_03_smith_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2220}, {"section": 4, "title": "More Trivia: Part 2", "readers": [6454], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/triviaandmo